{"id": 7098, "source": "pestle", "subject": "chemistry", "course": null, "level": "SL", "paper": "1", "year": "2017", "session": "17M", "subtopic": "1-3-reacting-masses-and-volumes", "title": "17M.1.SL.TZ2.3", "topic_id": "1", "source_url": "https://pestle.pages.dev/app/", "question_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>What is the maximum volume, in dm<sup>3</sup>, of CO<sub>2</sub>(g) produced when 1.00 g of CaCO<sub>3</sub>(s) reacts with 20.0 cm<sup>3</sup> of 2.00 mol<span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"\\,\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n</math></span>dm<sup>–3</sup> HCl(aq)?</p>\n<p>CaCO<sub>3</sub>(s) + 2HCl(aq) → CaCl<sub>2</sub>(aq) + H<sub>2</sub>O(l) + CO<sub>2</sub>(g)</p>\n<p>Molar volume of gas = 22.7 dm<sup>3</sup><span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"\\,\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n</math></span>mol<sup>–1</sup>; <em>M</em><sub>r</sub>(CaCO<sub>3</sub>) = 100.00</p>\n<p>A.     <span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"\\frac{1}{2} \\times \\frac{{20.0 \\times 2.0}}{{1000}} \\times 22.7\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<mfrac>\n<mn>1</mn>\n<mn>2</mn>\n</mfrac>\n<mo>×</mo>\n<mfrac>\n<mrow>\n<mn>20.0</mn>\n<mo>×</mo>\n<mn>2.0</mn>\n</mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mn>1000</mn>\n</mrow>\n</mfrac>\n<mo>×</mo>\n<mn>22.7</mn>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>B.     <span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"\\frac{{20.0 \\times 2.0}}{{1000}} \\times 22.7\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<mfrac>\n<mrow>\n<mn>20.0</mn>\n<mo>×</mo>\n<mn>2.0</mn>\n</mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mn>1000</mn>\n</mrow>\n</mfrac>\n<mo>×</mo>\n<mn>22.7</mn>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>C.     <span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"\\frac{{1.0}}{{100.00}} \\times 22.7\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<mfrac>\n<mrow>\n<mn>1.0</mn>\n</mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mn>100.00</mn>\n</mrow>\n</mfrac>\n<mo>×</mo>\n<mn>22.7</mn>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>D.     <span class=\"mjpage\